```sql
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        subscription_id,
        user_id,
        plan_id,
        started_at,
        ended_at,
        status
    FROM {{ ref('raw_subscriptions') }}
)
SELECT
    subscription_id,
    user_id,
    plan_id,
        CASE
            WHEN status = 'active' THEN true
            ELSE false
        END AS is_active,
        DATE_TRUNC('month', started_at) AS month,
        COALESCE(ended_at, CURRENT_DATE) AS subscription_end
FROM source
WHERE status IN ('active', 'past_due', 'cancelled')
```

-- int_deduped_billing.sql
```sql
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        subscription_id,
        event_month,
        amount,
        event_type,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY subscription_id, event_month
            ORDER BY event_id
        ) AS row_num
    FROM {{ ref('stg_billing_events') }}
)
SELECT
    subscription_id,
    event_month,
    amount,
    event_type
FROM source
WHERE row_num = 1
```

-- fct_subscription_metrics.sql
```sql
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        s.subscription_id,
        s.month,
        COALESCE(p.tier, '(unknown)') AS tier,
        COALESCE(c.industry, '(unknown)') AS industry,
        s.is_active
    FROM {{ ref('stg_subscriptions') }} s
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_plans') }} p
        ON s.plan_id = p.plan_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_users') }} u
        ON s.user_id = u.user_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('dim_companies') }} c
        ON u.company_id = c.company_id
)
SELECT
    month,
    tier,
    industry,
    COUNT(DISTINCT CASE WHEN is_active THEN subscription_id END) AS active_subscriptions,
    COALESCE(SUM(b.amount), 0) AS total_mrr,
    COUNT(DISTINCT u.user_id) AS unique_users
FROM source s
LEFT JOIN {{ ref('int_deduped_billing') }} b
    ON s.subscription_id = b.subscription_id
    AND s.month = b.event_month
GROUP BY
    month,
    tier,
    industry
ORDER BY
    month,
    tier,
    industry
